@startuml constrained-decode
' lling-llang grammar-constrained decoding pipeline:
'   CFG → PDA → compressed FSM → per-step token mask → masked LLM logits.
' Correction & NLP tier (amber) for the llm module; deep-learning tier (purple)
' for the LLM logit stage; foundation (blue) for the automaton artifacts; green
' for the accepted token. Palette: docs/diagrams/README.md.
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultTextAlignment center
skinparam ArrowColor #F9A825
skinparam ArrowThickness 1.3
skinparam activity {
  BackgroundColor #FFF59D
  BorderColor #F9A825
  FontColor #102027
  DiamondBackgroundColor #FFF59D
  DiamondBorderColor #F9A825
}
skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor #ECEFF1
  BorderColor #455A64
}

title <b>Grammar-constrained decoding pipeline</b>\n<size:11><i>CFG → PDA → compressed FSM → token mask <latex>m[v]=1 \text{ iff } v \in \text{allowed}</latex> → masked logits</i></size>

|#BBDEFB|compile (once)|
start
:CFG  <latex>G = (V, \Sigma, R, S)</latex>;
note right
  Context-free grammar:
  V variables · <latex>\Sigma</latex> terminals
  R rules · S start symbol
end note
:build PDA  <latex>(Q, \Sigma, \Gamma, \delta, q_0, Z_0)</latex>;
note right: stack <latex>\Gamma</latex> recognizes CFL nesting
:compress to FSM\n(precompute valid-token sets\n+ batch transitions);
:cache  valid_tokens[q] : TokenMask;

|#FFF59D|decode (per step)|
repeat
  :DecoderState s = (automaton_state, stack);
  :m ← valid_tokens(s)   // <latex>m[v] = 1 \text{ iff } v \in \text{allowed}</latex>;
  |#E1BEE7|LLM|
  :logits <latex>\ell</latex> over vocabulary V;
  :<latex>\ell'[v]</latex> ← <latex>\ell[v] \text{ if } m[v]=1 \text{ else } -\infty</latex>;
  :sample / argmax  token t  with <latex>m[t]=1</latex>;
  |#FFF59D|decode (per step)|
  :s ← advance(s, t)   // PDA push/pop or FSM step;
backward :more tokens & <latex>\lnot</latex>is_accepting(s)?;
repeat while (continue) is (yes) not (no)
#C8E6C9:accepted sequence <latex>\in L(G)</latex>;
stop
@enduml
